{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3494022,"name":"","username":"GriffM","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/22d042/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-01-27T21:00:40.577Z","cooked":"<p>Hi ChiefDelphi! I’m the programming captain for 1923. We’ve been using a state machine type system to control our robots for the past 2 years. Over the 2024 offseason, we changed up our implementation, and I’m wondering what more experienced <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span> programmers think of it.</p>
<p>This is our 2024 offseason codebase: <a href="https://github.com/Team1923/2024OffseasonRewrite" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">GitHub - Team1923/2024OffseasonRewrite</a></p>
<p>In the past, we’ve done all of our state handling logic in the respective subsystems’ periodic loops. In the offseason, we designed commands, where the state handling is done in their execute methods. Then, we set these state machine commands as our subsystems’ default commands. The goal behind this is to make it easy to override the statemachine, for example when trying to temporarily control an arm with a joystick instead of states.</p>
<p>Here’s an example of the flow:</p>
<p>We call a shoot gamepiece command to set our statehandler’s desired states for all related subsystems (<a href="https://github.com/Team1923/2024OffseasonRewrite/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/scoring/ShootGamePiece.java" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">2024OffseasonRewrite/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/scoring/ShootGamePiece.java at main · Team1923/2024OffseasonRewrite · GitHub</a>)</p>
<p>Our arm state machine handles those states. Our philosophy was to make the state machine act as a restrictor (not letting the robot do anything that would put it in an undesirable state), and also to handle ‘weird’ cases, like motor control requests that aren’t just a set and forget (dynamic, may have a timer involved).</p><aside class="onebox githubblob" data-onebox-src="https://github.com/Team1923/2024OffseasonRewrite/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/statecommands/ArmStateMachine.java">
